<item>
            <title>[LU-3439] User code creating multiple lockfiles with same name</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3439</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Not sure if this a known issue already, but we have a user who noticed they can create identical filenames within a single directory via their home-grown locking mechanism. We have worked with them to create a small reproducer which shows the issue on 6 Lustre clients (96 MPI tasks).  The net effect of running this test is creation of duplicate filenames:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;{{c558-801$ ls -l lockdir/&lt;br/&gt;
total 12&lt;br/&gt;
---------- 1 karl G-800747 52 Jun  5 08:39 Lockfile.lck&lt;br/&gt;
---------- 1 karl G-800747 52 Jun  5 08:39 Lockfile.lck&lt;br/&gt;
---------- 1 karl G-800747 52 Jun  5 08:39 Lockfile.lck}}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tarball attached with user code and example output from our Stampede environment. We can confirm that we do not get the repeat filenames when running the reproducer on Lustre 1.8.6&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre: 2.1.5&lt;br/&gt;
OFED: 1.5.4.1&lt;br/&gt;
Kernel:  2.6.32-279.el6.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
</environment>
